result.execSummary:
The defendant Mandy Ann Mckillip was found guilty of the following charge(s) in this case. One or more other charges in this case were dismissed. The dismissed charges were not proven and have no legal effect. Mandy Ann Mckillip is presumed innocent of the dismissed charges.

  • Mandy Ann Mckillip was found guilty of Sexual Intercourse with Child 16 or Older, Actor 19 or Older, a class A misdemeanor, Wisconsin Statutes 948.09.
  • Mandy Ann Mckillip was found guilty of Intent. Contribute/Delinquency Child, a class A misdemeanor, Wisconsin Statutes 948.40(1).
  • Mandy Ann Mckillip was found guilty of Intent. Contribute/Delinquency Child, a class A misdemeanor, Wisconsin Statutes 948.40(1).

Notice to employers: It may be a violation of state law to discriminate against a job applicant because of an arrest or conviction record. Generally speaking, an employer may refuse to hire an applicant on the basis of a conviction only if the circumstances of the conviction substantially relate to the particular job.
